Program: Discovery
Title: Cassini-Huygens Probe - running rings around Saturn
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jryvl
Last Broadcast Date: 20 December 2004
A report on one of the most ambitious interplanetary probes of our time. Richard Hollingham follows the progress of the Cassini-Huygens probe, sent to look at the planet Saturn and its moons. The 1.5 billion kilometre journey took the probe through some of the worst conditions in the solar system.